Log in to your AgentClash account by verifying the login in your browser.

The CLI prints a verification link, opens it in your default browser when possible,
and waits for you to approve the login in your AgentClash instance.

For headless or remote shells, pass --device to print the link without auto-opening.
Pass --force to create a fresh CLI token even when you are already logged in.
For CI/CD, set the AGENTCLASH_TOKEN environment variable instead.

Usage:
  agentclash auth login [flags]

Flags:
      --device   Print the verification URL instead of opening the browser automatically
      --force    Start a new browser login even if existing credentials are valid
  -h, --help     help for login

Global Flags:
      --api-url string     API base URL (overrides config)
      --json               Output in JSON format
      --no-color           Disable color output
      --non-interactive    Disable interactive prompts (also honored: CI=true, AGENTCLASH_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, --json, no TTY)
  -o, --output string      Output format: table, json, yaml
  -q, --quiet              Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose            Enable debug output on stderr
  -w, --workspace string   Workspace ID (overrides config)
      --yes                Skip confirmation prompts
